The '''Água Preta virus''' is probably a [[herpesvirus|herpes-like virus]] as determined by thin-section electron microscopy. It was isolated from a species of [[bat]], [[Carolloa subrufa]], in the [[Utinga Forest]] near [[Belem]], [[Brazil]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Mahy|first=Brian W J|title=A dictionary of virology|date=2001|publisher=Academic Press|location=San Diego, Calif. [u.a.]|isbn=978-0-12-465327-6|pages=9|edition=3.}}</ref>

