{{Infobox scientist |name = Victor Sterki |image = |image_size = |alt = |caption = Victor Sterki |birth_date = 1846<!--{{Birth date|1846|??|??}}--> |birth_place = [[Solothurn]], Switzerland |death_date = <!--{{Death date and age|1933|??|??|1846|??|??}}--> {{Death year and age|1933|1846}} |death_place = |residence = [[Ohio]] |citizenship = |nationality = |ethnicity = |fields = [[malacology]] |workplaces = |alma_mater = [[University of Bern]] and [[Munich University]]<ref name="carnegiemnh.org"/> |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |notable_students = |known_for = research in [[Pupillidae]] and in [[Sphaeriidae]]<ref name="carnegiemnh.org"/> |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |awards = |footnotes = }}
'''Victor Sterki''' (1846 in [[Solothurn]], Switzerland - 1933)<ref name="carnegiemnh.org">[http://www.carnegiemnh.org/mollusks/sterki.html "Victor Sterki"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927151032/http://www.carnegiemnh.org/mollusks/sterki.html |date=2011-09-27 }}. [[Carnegie Museum of Natural History]], accessed 23 April 2011.</ref> was a [[malacologist]] from [[Switzerland]] who lived in the [[United States]].<ref>Coan E. V., Kabat A. R. & Petit R. E. (15 February 2011). [http://www.malacological.org/publications/2400_malacology.php ''2,400 years of malacology, 8th ed.''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111161316/http://www.malacological.org/publications/2400_malacology.php |date=2012-11-11 }}, 936 pp. + 42 pp. [Annex of Collations]. American Malacological Society</ref>
He worked as an assistant in the Section of Invertebrates in the [[Carnegie Museum of Natural History]] from 1909 to 1933.<ref name="carnegiemnh.org"/>
Malacological collections by Sterki of [[Pupillidae]] has 4000 lots and of [[Sphaeriidae]] has 12,000 lots.<ref name="carnegiemnh.org"/> Both collections are deposited in the [[Carnegie Museum of Natural History]].<ref name="carnegiemnh.org"/>
The malacological journal [[Sterkiana]] and the land snail species ''[[Guppya sterkii]]'' were named after him.<ref name=Malacologists>[http://www.inhs.uiuc.edu/~ksc/Malacologists/SterkiV.html Victor Sterki]</ref><ref>[[Henry Augustus Pilsbry|Pilsbry H. A.]] (1946). [[s:Page:Land Mollusca of North America (north of Mexico) Vol. II Part 1 (1st half).pdf/256|''Land Mollusca of North America (north of Mexico), vol. II part 1'']], 1946, pg. 246.</ref>
